  "texts": [
    "We will describe how we use the SOC in this section and leave a detailed description of other supplementary lists in Appendix B.",
    "First, the SOC contains 23 occupation groups with each group encompassing multiple occupation titles.",
    "For example, the Computer and Mathematical Occupations group includes occupation titles such as software developer, data scientist, and mathematician.",
    "We expanded the list to be more inclusive by incorporating abbreviations and occupations that frequently appear on Twitter but are not initially included in the SOC.",
    "For example, we added abbreviations such as CEO, prof, and tech as well as occupations such as student, founder, and YouTuber."
